60
00:05:40,648 --> 00:05:42,946
- Real fast, and good intensity.
- High intensity.

61
00:05:43,017 --> 00:05:45,247
Great, 'cause
I was like really fast.

62
00:05:45,319 --> 00:05:48,152
The preparation was good.
I think that's your specialty.

63
00:05:48,222 --> 00:05:51,988
If I said that, it would sound
like bragging. Okay, criticisms.

64
00:05:52,059 --> 00:05:55,085
- Criticisms.
- I've only one: not very thorough.

65
00:05:55,162 --> 00:05:57,858
- Left a lot of valuables.
- I don't think that was a mistake.

66
00:05:57,932 --> 00:06:01,424
That was one of the limitations
of this job.

67
00:06:01,502 --> 00:06:03,766
By the way, great job in there.

68
00:06:03,838 --> 00:06:06,705
- It was nice working with you, 'cause...
- Thank you.

69
00:06:08,743 --> 00:06:10,734
Next order of business: Mr. Henry.

70
00:06:10,811 --> 00:06:14,440
You're probably wondering when
I'm going to introduce you to Mr. Henry.

71
00:06:14,515 --> 00:06:18,007
In answer to that question, very soon.
In fact, judging from how well that...

72
00:06:18,085 --> 00:06:20,076
Here you go.
You gotta do that.

73
00:06:20,154 --> 00:06:22,452
Judging from how well
that job went today...

74
00:06:22,523 --> 00:06:24,320
including the coins and earrings...

75
00:06:24,392 --> 00:06:26,383
was, to say the least...

76
00:06:28,729 --> 00:06:31,926
You took the earrings, Dignan?
You took 'em?

77
00:06:34,936 --> 00:06:39,066
Well, it's my fault. Ultimately,
Anthony, when are you gonna learn?

78
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:42,701
Man, you got another ball!
Should I play your game?

79
00:06:42,777 --> 00:06:45,769
I know you remember the list,
'cause you signed it.

80
00:06:45,846 --> 00:06:48,610
"The things Dignan's
not supposed to touch."

81
00:06:48,683 --> 00:06:51,914
I can't be sorting through all that shit
in the middle of a burglary.

82
00:06:51,986 --> 00:06:55,945
Hey, I don't care, okay? I bought
the earrings for my mother's birthday.

83
00:06:56,023 --> 00:06:58,116
I went down,
I picked 'em out myself.

84
00:06:58,192 --> 00:07:01,423
Hey, one thing is, every valuable item
in the house was on that list.

85
00:07:01,495 --> 00:07:04,055
Maybe we should've robbed your house.
Did you ever think of that?

86
00:07:04,131 --> 00:07:06,622
I bet that never crossed your mind.

87
00:07:07,702 --> 00:07:11,103
What? What? Come on, Dignan!

88
00:07:11,172 --> 00:07:13,106
You know there's nothing
to steal from my mom and Craig.

89
00:07:27,822 --> 00:07:29,551
Hey, Grace!

90
00:07:34,962 --> 00:07:37,021
You're supposed to be in Arizona.

91
00:07:37,098 --> 00:07:39,293
What, you don't say hi anymore?
Come on.

92
00:07:39,367 --> 00:07:41,597
Is this the...
Are you the pilot?

93
00:07:41,669 --> 00:07:44,433
No, I'm Anthony.
I'm Grace's brother.

94
00:07:44,505 --> 00:07:47,235
Will you excuse us
for a minute, Bernice?

95
00:07:47,308 --> 00:07:49,640
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

96
00:07:52,980 --> 00:07:54,914
You told her...

97
00:07:54,982 --> 00:07:57,974
You told your friend Bernice
I'm some kind of jet pilot?

98
00:07:58,052 --> 00:08:01,579
What was I supposed to say,
they stuck you in an insane asylum?

99
00:08:01,655 --> 00:08:05,989
It wasn't an insane asylum, Grace.
I explained it was for exhaustion.

100
00:08:06,060 --> 00:08:07,857
Exhaustion?

101
00:08:07,928 --> 00:08:09,623
Yes, exhaustion.

102
00:08:09,697 --> 00:08:13,827
You haven't worked a day in your life.
How could you be exhausted?

103
00:08:13,901 --> 00:08:16,028
Okay, sit down. Okay?

104
00:08:16,103 --> 00:08:20,039
I didn't come up here today
to argue with you, okay?

105
00:08:22,009 --> 00:08:25,945
- I got some friends waiting for me...
- Who?

106
00:08:27,081 --> 00:08:29,208
- Some associates.
- Dignan?

107
00:08:30,451 --> 00:08:33,318
Yeah, Dignan, but also...

108
00:08:34,221 --> 00:08:37,054
What's wrong with Dignan, Grace?
I thought you liked Dignan.

109
00:08:37,124 --> 00:08:40,025
- I do like Dignan.
- Then why did you sigh?

110
00:08:40,094 --> 00:08:41,618
But he's a liar.

111
00:08:41,695 --> 00:08:41,729
Bob Mapplethorpe,
potential getaway driver, go!

112
00:08:41,729 --> 00:08:44,391
Bob Mapplethorpe,
potential getaway driver, go!

113
00:08:45,299 --> 00:08:47,859
- Go.
- There's an air of mystery about me.

114
00:08:47,935 --> 00:08:51,200
Don't complicate it. Your strength is
you have a car you can provide.

115
00:08:51,272 --> 00:08:54,571
Sell yourself. Start over.
You ready? Go.

116
00:08:54,642 --> 00:08:57,406
Okay. All right.
I'm a risk taker.

117
00:08:57,478 --> 00:09:01,175
I'm growin' an entire crop of marijuana
plants in my parents' back yard.

118
00:09:01,248 --> 00:09:04,740
Wait a second. You're growing an entire
crop of marijuana in your back yard?

119
00:09:04,819 --> 00:09:08,050
Dignan, look. I'm just not that good
at this selling yourself stuff, okay?

120
00:09:08,122 --> 00:09:10,420
So I'm just
gonna tell you the truth.

121
00:09:10,491 --> 00:09:13,153
I really want to be
a part of this team...

122
00:09:13,227 --> 00:09:16,162
and I'm the only one
with a car.

123
00:09:17,398 --> 00:09:19,059
That's good.

124
00:09:20,234 --> 00:09:22,429
'Cause that hits me right here.

125
00:09:22,503 --> 00:09:26,166
Okay, can you do me a favor
and take...

126
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:30,643
I want you to take these earrings
and put them in Mom's mahogany box.

127
00:09:30,711 --> 00:09:34,738
- Put them in your backpack.
- What are you doing with these?

128
00:09:34,815 --> 00:09:37,181
Could you just put them
in the box, please, Grace?

129
00:09:37,251 --> 00:09:41,950
You've really gotten into the bad habit
of asking a huge amount of questions.

130
00:09:44,358 --> 00:09:45,791
God.

131
00:09:47,228 --> 00:09:48,957
I gotta go, okay, pal?

132
00:09:49,029 --> 00:09:51,327
What's gonna happen to you, Anthony?

133
00:09:51,398 --> 00:09:55,300
Geez, Grace, what the hell
kind of question is that to ask me?

134
00:09:55,369 --> 00:09:57,303
When are you coming home?

135
00:10:01,242 --> 00:10:05,269
Grace, I can't come home.
I'm an adult.

136
00:10:08,182 --> 00:10:12,881
Why you looking at me
like that? Huh?

137
00:10:12,953 --> 00:10:16,047
When I was little, I wanted to know
what caused thunder...

138
00:10:16,123 --> 00:10:19,456
How'd it go with Grace?
How'd it go?

139
00:10:19,527 --> 00:10:21,552
- Can we leave, please, Bob?
- Sure.

140
00:10:23,364 --> 00:10:26,561
Little kids are really cute.
She is a cute little kid.

141
00:10:26,634 --> 00:10:31,162
What happened? I just have no idea.
I mean, how did Grace get so cynical?

142
00:10:31,238 --> 00:10:35,004
I can't answer that now. My only concern
is getting you back in the car.

143
00:10:35,075 --> 00:10:38,238
- She's come to this conclusion...
- Get back in the car where you can...

144
00:10:38,312 --> 00:10:43,249
- She thinks I'm a failure.
- What? She said you were a failure?

145
00:10:43,317 --> 00:10:45,547
What has she ever accomplished
with her life?

146
00:10:45,619 --> 00:10:48,087
- What do I do?
- You don't have to do anything.

147
00:10:48,155 --> 00:10:51,022
I'm not saying that
she has to look up to me at all.

148
00:10:51,091 --> 00:10:54,492
- Don't worry about it.
- Maybe she should. Why not?

149
00:10:54,562 --> 00:10:58,498
- She told her friend I was a pilot.
- Stop for a second and look at this.

150
00:10:58,566 --> 00:11:01,399
- Oh, no.
- Fact: I learned more...

151
00:11:01,468 --> 00:11:03,561
in the two months
I spent with Mr. Henry...

152
00:11:03,637 --> 00:11:06,265
than I learned in 15 years
of academic study.

153
00:11:06,340 --> 00:11:09,275
Fact: I can guarantee you,
after Mr. Henry sees us pull this job...

154
00:11:09,343 --> 00:11:12,039
he's gonna take a personal interest
in our future.

155
00:11:12,112 --> 00:11:14,273
Fact: Mr. Henry
drives a Jaguar.

156
00:11:14,348 --> 00:11:16,976
Fact: The picture's
not doing it for me right now.

157
00:11:17,051 --> 00:11:20,248
Well, does the fact that
I'm trying to do it do it for you?

158
00:11:20,321 --> 00:11:22,346
I hate to interrupt
your conversation, guys...

159
00:11:22,423 --> 00:11:25,153
but I think I know
what you've been going through...

160
00:11:25,226 --> 00:11:27,660
'cause I've been through
some pretty heavy shit myself.

161
00:11:27,728 --> 00:11:30,561
If you're feeling alone,
like nobody in the world cares...

162
00:11:30,631 --> 00:11:34,123
and nobody in the fucking world
gives a shit, then I'm here.

163
00:11:34,201 --> 00:11:36,362
- That was a stop sign.
- I'm ready to listen, man.

164
00:11:36,437 --> 00:11:38,371
If you want,
I'll even open up first.

165
00:11:38,439 --> 00:11:42,739
My brother... That's a shit situation.
He beats the crap out of me always.

166
00:11:49,550 --> 00:11:52,678
I don't suppose either of you know
why Bob's car is parked out front.

167
00:11:52,753 --> 00:11:55,313
Yeah, he's here.

168
00:11:55,389 --> 00:11:57,448
- He's ins...
- He's here at the house.

169
00:11:57,524 --> 00:11:59,458
Let me see if Bob's
keeping the pool clean.

170
00:11:59,526 --> 00:12:01,653
- That's Future Man.
- Yeah, I know.

171
00:12:05,299 --> 00:12:07,233
What the fuck is this?

172
00:12:08,068 --> 00:12:12,528
Vamanos, Clay. Bob, you were told to
thoroughly clean the pool this morning.

173
00:12:12,606 --> 00:12:14,540
- It's a leaf.
- It was one leaf!

174
00:12:16,110 --> 00:12:18,044
Your name's Anthony, isn't it?

175
00:12:18,112 --> 00:12:20,842
Yeah, his name's Anthony.
My name's Dignan.

176
00:12:20,914 --> 00:12:23,883
I'm Stacy Sinclair,
Elizabeth's sorority sister.

177
00:12:23,951 --> 00:12:27,045
I didn't know
she had a sister.

178
00:12:27,121 --> 00:12:30,056
Oh, my God.
You have the best sense of humor.

179
00:12:30,124 --> 00:12:33,389
She is going to be so jealous
I saw you here.

180
00:12:33,460 --> 00:12:36,691
So, you go to school
in Arizona, right?

181
00:12:36,764 --> 00:12:40,632
- No, I was in the hospital.
- Oh, what for?

182
00:12:43,570 --> 00:12:45,834
I went nuts.

183
00:12:45,906 --> 00:12:49,239
- He's kidding. He didn't go nuts.
- You poor thing. How'd it happen?

184
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:52,871
- Do you really wanna know?
- Yes, I really do.

185
00:12:56,216 --> 00:12:59,413
One morning
over at Elizabeth's beach house...

186
00:12:59,486 --> 00:13:04,150
she asked me if I'd rather
go water skiing or lay out.

187
00:13:04,224 --> 00:13:08,786
And I realized that not only did I
not want to answer that question...

188
00:13:08,862 --> 00:13:12,764
but I never wanted to answer
another water-sports question...

189
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:16,325
or see any of these people again
for the rest of my life.

190
00:13:17,871 --> 00:13:21,329
Three days later I was on my way
out to the desert, and that was that.

191
00:13:23,344 --> 00:13:25,403
Bullying son of a bitch!

192
00:13:25,479 --> 00:13:28,812
You're calling me a bully?
Here's a bully for ya!

193
00:13:31,552 --> 00:13:34,020
Hold on, Bob! You're only
gonna make this take longer!

194
00:13:34,088 --> 00:13:36,147
You're really complicated,
aren't you?

195
00:13:36,223 --> 00:13:38,919
- My ear!
- I try not to be.

196
00:14:18,465 --> 00:14:21,400
Okay, escape route is crucial...

197
00:14:21,468 --> 00:14:24,904
in case somebody is tailing us
or even chasing us, as the case may be.

198
00:14:24,972 --> 00:14:27,236
We can't be sure
how it is gonna happen.

199
00:14:27,307 --> 00:14:29,502
Do you think
we're gonna be chased?

200
00:14:29,576 --> 00:14:32,568
That's a good question.
No, I don't think we're gonna be chased.

201
00:14:32,646 --> 00:14:35,774
I'm just being hypocritical here.
However, I will say...

202
00:14:35,849 --> 00:14:39,910
Bob, please don't interrupt me, man,
'cause I'm trying to stay focused.

203
00:14:39,987 --> 00:14:44,356
You're responsible for the external
situation, streets and the getaway.

204
00:14:44,425 --> 00:14:48,327
Excuse me. Are the explosives
really necessary here?

205
00:14:48,395 --> 00:14:51,728
I think it would be a lot more simple if
I just walked up to the door alone.

206
00:14:51,799 --> 00:14:54,495
- I think that would be...
- Why are you undermining me?

207
00:14:54,568 --> 00:14:57,935
How many bullets does this thing take?
Look, I'm paying attention.

208
00:14:58,005 --> 00:15:01,441
Goddamn it! You're not paying attention
if you're messing around with the gun!

209
00:15:01,508 --> 00:15:04,306
Now, quit... Anthony,
keep the gun on the table.

210
00:15:04,378 --> 00:15:05,811
Look, Dignan, relax.

211
00:15:05,879 --> 00:15:08,507
I can't focus
unless the gun is on the table.

212
00:15:08,582 --> 00:15:10,641
- I paid for it.
- Shut up, man!

213
00:15:10,717 --> 00:15:12,912
I'm warning you now.
Be quiet, please.

214
00:15:12,986 --> 00:15:16,444
- It's true. I paid for the gun.
- Say it one more time.

215
00:15:16,523 --> 00:15:19,185
Say it again.
Repeat what you just said.

216
00:15:21,495 --> 00:15:23,292
I paid for the gun.

217
00:15:30,103 --> 00:15:32,663
He's out. You're out too.

218
00:15:32,739 --> 00:15:34,707
- And I don't think I'm in, either.
- Calm down.

219
00:15:34,775 --> 00:15:37,938
No gang!
You two just don't give a shit.

220
00:15:38,011 --> 00:15:41,344
When it comes right down to it,
you don't care.

221
00:15:41,415 --> 00:15:44,282
How does an asshole like Bob
get such a great kitchen?

222
00:16:00,234 --> 00:16:03,761
I apologize.
That was poor leadership.

223
00:16:03,837 --> 00:16:07,034
I'm under a lot of pressure
right now, and...

224
00:16:08,375 --> 00:16:11,071
I don't feel like the team
is gelling the way...

225
00:16:11,144 --> 00:16:14,341
if I can even use that word, 'cause
I don't even know if we are a team.

226
00:16:14,414 --> 00:16:17,315
